condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule I, Section I, C (Project Agreement) | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than six (6) monthsafter effective date, issue the Matching Grants Manual, in form and substance acceptable to the Bank | Due Date :16-Dec-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule I, Section III, A (Project Agreement) | Description :The Implementing Entity shall ensure that allprocurement activities of the Project shall be audited every year, under terms of reference satisfactory to the Association byindependent auditors. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II, B, 2 (Financial Agreement) | Description :the Recipient shall ensure that interimunaudited financial reports for the Project are prepared and furnished to the Association not later than 45 days after the end ofeach calendar quarter | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II, B, 3 (Financial Agreement) | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall haveits Financial Statements audited by independent auditors no later than 6 months after the end of each fiscal year | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section II, B, 4 (Financial Agreement) | Description :(iv) The Project Implementing Entity shallensure that auditors are employed not later than three (3) months after the Effective Date. | Due Date :16-Nov-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule II, Section V (Financial Agreement | Description :Evidence showing that the Recipient has budgeted andallocated to the Project Implementing Entity counterpart funds in amounts required for Project implementation during said calendaryear. | Frequency :Yearly
